fr.sorbonne_u.components.hem2025.tests_utils

Class SimulationTestStep

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.components.hem2025.tests_utils.SimulationTestStep

  • public class SimulationTestStep
extends java.lang.Object
    The class TestStep implements a description of a test action to be taken as part of a scenario.

    Description

    A test step is executed by a simulation model designated by its URI at some instant, its time of occurrence. The time management used in test steps and tests scenario is based on two time lines. Test actions are planned using the class Instant. A test scenario has a start instant and an end instant. The time of occurrence of a test step is an instant between the start and end instants. This time line of instants is mapped to the time line of the simulation clock represented by the class Time of the simulation framework.

    The test action per se is organised following the DEVS protocol for internal transitions. It is composed of:

    • an output function that generates the array list of events to be exported at the defined internal transition,
    • an internal transition function that performs the modifications of the state of the model according to the sought action.

    The output function takes the reference to the simulation model and the simulated time of occurrence; it returns an array list of events as does the method output in the framework. The internal transition function also takes as argument the reference to the simulation model and the simulated time of occurrence of the transition but does not return a result as it works by side effects on the simulation model.

    The above ingredients of a test step are initialised at creation time by th constructor. The class defines the methods generateOutput and performInternalTransition that execute their respective function.
